<font size=2>
This is whats been found so far... <br> <br> <br> <br> <br>                       The note we take to Camin has four items on it - <br> <br>                       'Dragon bones - Plane of Fear' : Suspected to be found on Dragoliche.  <br>                       'Jet Black egg' - Unknown' : No ideas as of yet.  <br>                       Mistletoe powder - Old Sebilis' : Found on Tolapmulj. LORE ITEM - NO DROP.  <br>                       'Rune of Lost Thought - Unknown' : No ideas as of yet.  <br>                       Camin can be found at the Vasty Deep Inn within Erudin. To find him inside the Inn, <br>                       open the front door to the Inn and go up the stairs on your right. Follow the <br>                       hallway around the second floor and Camin is found behind the first door upon your <br>                       left. Off the bat, he is normally indifferent or apprehensive to everyone. To raise <br>                       faction, hand him the note that was given to you by Soloman and you will receive <br>                       the following faction adjustments: <br> <br>                       TrueSpirit (positive faction)  <br>                       Camin will now reply with - <br> <br>                       Camin says, 'So you have met Solomen, eh? He is a man with a wealth of <br>                       knowledge. It is good to hear he is well. <br> <br>                       Now hail Camin and he will respond with this - <br> <br>                       Camin says 'Go away! I have no time for you!  <br> <br>                       If this happens, you need to raise your faction to warmly with him. The easiest way <br>                       to do so is the following:  <br> <br>                       Go back to Solusek Ro and bind yourself at Solomen.  <br>                       you say 'I agree.' Solomen will hand you the note to take back to Camin.  <br>                       Gate to Tox and run to Erudin.  <br>                       Hand Camin the note and get positive faction with TrueSpirit.  <br>                       Do this until you are warmly with Camin. (approx. 20 times)  <br>                       Once you are warmly with Camin:  <br> <br>                       you say, 'What are you searching for?' <br>                       Camin says 'Ah! A smart one, I see! If you really wish to know about such a thing, <br>                       you will have to help me finance my studies. The knowledge I have acquired and <br>                       researched did not come cheaply. <br> <br>                       At this point, hand Camin 1000 platinum pieces. Doing this will make Camin reply <br>                       with: <br> <br>                       Camin says, 'Good, good, you show a willingness to learn of this with your offer. <br>                       What I can tell you is that Solusek Ro had four followers who had shown <br>                       exceptional aptitude in the arts of wizardry. Solusek Ro himself tutored them. He <br>                       considered them to be like his own children. I know of one who still exists. He goes <br>                       by the name of Arantir Karondor. He used to specialize in the storing of magic into <br>                       physical objects. Arantir has been hiding for many, many years and will most <br>                       assuredly be going by another name, so keep your eyes open. Anyway, be off, I <br>                       need to continue my research. Return to me if you ever find Arantir Karondor.' <br> <br>                       Now to find Arantir Karondor. I honestly have no idea what Verant was thinking <br>                       when they did this part of the quest. There are zero clues as to who or where this <br>                       person is and honestly, it's sort of disturbing to me that every other class' quest is <br>                       straightforward, but still has a very good degree of difficulty. None the less, there <br>                       is a female NPC vendor in Halas named 'Dargon' that sells a potion called Ro's <br>                       Breath (8 Charges of Shield of Lava, MAGIC, LORE, NO DROP). She is located in <br>                       front of the Shaman guild. Purchase this potion from Dargon (evil races be warned - <br>                       you ARE KOS!) for the sum of about 900pp to 1100pp depending on your faction <br>                       and charisma. <br> <br>                       Now take this potion back to Camin in Erudin and hand it to him. He will reply with <br>                       the following: <br> <br>                       Camin says 'Very interesting... I've seen this work before. Yes, yes! It's the work of <br>                       Arantir Karondor! Give this back to the person you got it from. Maybe he will have a <br>                       clue to Arantir's location.'  <br> <br>                       Camin gives you back the potion and you must take it back to Dargon in Halas. <br>                       Note: you cannot skip the previous trip to Camin. You absolutely, must hand the <br>                       potion to Camin. If you try to skip the trip to Erudin, you will get the following <br>                       message from Dargon: &quot;I didnt request this item, but thank you very much&quot;. <br> <br>                       Back in Halas, hand the Ro's Breath potion back to Dargon. She will turn into blue <br>                       robe adorned, Arantir Karondor and reply with: <br> <br>                       Dargon says 'So, I've been discovered! You must know Camin - he is one of the <br>                       only people who could have recognized my work. I have worked very hard to mask <br>                       my presence here.'  <br> <br>                       You say, 'hail Arantir Karondor'  <br>                       Arantir Karondor says 'Before I tell you anything, I require you to help me. Seek a <br>                       woman named Challice. Give her this letter and then return to me.' <br> <br>                       The letter that Arantir hands you is actually a ring. Identifying it reveals: &quot;Item <br>                       Lore: My love has no bounds.&quot; Challice is found in the basement of the Felwithe <br>                       paladin guild. Hand Challice the ring and she will reply with: <br> <br>                       Challice says 'Oh yes? Arantir? What a fool he was! the man gave me everything, <br>                       but for all his intelligence, he could never understand why I was truly with him. It <br>                       was for his power; he could do anything. But when he mysteriously lost it, he <br>                       became just another toy. I never loved him. Return this ring to him. He will <br>                       understand that I have no desire to see him again.'  <br> <br>                       This new ring, when indentified reads: &quot;Item Lore: I never could love a man like <br>                       you.&quot; Take this ring back to Arantir and hand it over (you can hand it to either <br>                       Dargon or Arantir). Then you must hail him to get his attention and go through the <br>                       following dialogue: <br> <br>                       you say, 'Hail Arantir Karondor!' <br>                       Arantir Karondor says 'Ah, but it pains my heart to see this. How I could love a <br>                       women like that is beyond me. And yet, I still do love her. It was on the day I was <br>                       to ask her to marry me that I lost my powers. When I was about to cast my <br>                       greatest spell to prove my love to her, my magic failed. She ran out on me that <br>                       day. But enough of me, do you wish to hear my story?'  <br> <br>                       you say, 'I wish to hear your story.' <br>                       Arantir Karondor says 'I once was one of four true followers of Solusek Ro. So great <br>                       were the four of us that Solusek Ro himself made us each a special item. We did <br>                       not know what the others' items were, but we realized that was for our own <br>                       safety. Each one of us, after receiving the item, began to plot against Solusek Ro. <br>                       Each of us believed we had enough power to dominate Norrath. Solusek Ro saw this <br>                       and at the time we needed our powers most, he stripped us of them. Now I know <br>                       two of the other wizards by name. One was called Sylen Tyrn, the other's name <br>                       was Demunir Scry. The last wizard was a gnome, but I can't think of his name. <br> <br>                       you say, 'What about Sylen Tyrn?' <br>                       Arantir Karondor says 'Sylen was a high elf wizard, and like many high elves, he <br>                       believed himself to be better than others. Because of his birth, he thought he was <br>                       more noble and more intelligent than anyone else. I heard how met his demise - <br>                       while flying over a vast area of water, his powers were stripped from him in <br>                       midflight. He fell and was captured by a rival wizard who specialized in magics of <br>                       the water. Search for that wizard and you could find a trace of Sylen. <br> <br>                       More than likely, the 'trace' of Sylen Tyrn is found off of Phiningel Autropos deep in <br>                       Kedge Keep - the Blue Crystal Staff. When this item is identified, the power of <br>                       Solusek Ro radiates from within. <br> <br>                       you say, 'What about Demunir Scry?' <br>                       Arantir Karondor says 'Demunir was a human in a rush for power. He was extremely <br>                       intelligent and resourceful but, unfortunately, was more interested in destructive <br>                       magic. Hearing of an ancient land, he immediately traveled to it, believing there to <br>                       be powerful relics left undiscovered there. While exploring, he came upon a dwelling <br>                       that housed a powerful warrior. Believing himself to be more powerful, he attempted <br>                       to take this dwelling for himself. While in battle with this warrior, Solusek Ro stole <br>                       his powers and left him helpless. It is said that Demunir's item is the warrior's most <br>                       prized trophy. <br> <br>                       The Demunir item is thought to either be the Gnarled Staff off of Venril Sathir from <br>                       within Karnor's Castle or a warrior item found from deep within The Hole. <br> <br>                       you say, 'What about the gnome?' <br>                       Arantir Karondor says 'Ah, the gnome I know very little about. I know he was small <br>                       and crafty, and that he had a brother. His brother's craft was that of making <br>                       fireworks, and he was the unfortunate victim of one of his own experiments. His <br>                       firework exploded, leaving his mind diminished in capacity, even for a gnome. I <br>                       remember others calling him 'Old Stewpot' in jest. I do not know if this is his birth <br>                       name, but it may help you to locate him. I hear he also stays close to water <br>                       because of the explosion. You never know when another gnomish invention will go <br>                       awry. Give him this letter to help motivate him to remember.  <br> <br>                       The gnome seems to be Kandin Firepot. Kandin can be found in the Southwest <br>                       region of ButcherBlock Mountains (-1500 +2800) near the ocean. Handing Kandin <br>                       the note from Arantir results in the following: <br> <br>                       Kandin Firepot says 'Brother! I have one of those. He's great, but he's dead. His <br>                       name was Gabstik and he was a really powerful wizard. I still have one of his <br>                       greatest possessions! Hey, I know! You can help me with my greatest firework! I <br>                       need you to get me a skin to put the powder from my firework in. That's the only <br>                       thing I can think of to use though I cannot get myself. I need a skin that is dry and <br>                       brittle, yet can still be shaped. So go fetch me some and I'll scratch your back. <br> <br> <br>                       Thats as far as anyone has got. Hope this helps.  <br> <br>Xein Niex <br>Guild Runt <br>&quot;While Xyzz lays down and bleeds...I shall flee&quot;

